*.*                        -> for all show all extention files
*(wildcard)

ls                         -> for cureent directory content
ls dir_name/               -> for see direct content of any folder or directory like (ls Downloads/)
ls /                       -> for see list of root directory
ls ..                      -> for one step back in dir
ls ../..                   -> for two step back in dir
ls -l                      -> list with authorize permission & full details(time,size...etc)
ls -a                      -> for seeing hidden files (.file_name)
ls -s                      -> for sorting the files in asending order , this is also valid (ls -sl)
ls folder_name/*.extention -> for seeing specify extention files  , for example (ls Downloads/*.deb)
ls *.extention             -> Is also for seeing specify extention file but in this case you should want to 
                              stay the same directory 
ls -flag > file_name.txt   -> for saving the output of the command file name what you want
ls -d */                   -> for seeing all the directories                       
ls -R                      -> for directory structure
